Name: Ash Weight
Description: The ash that is left over after baking and is the INORGANIC contents of the sample

Name: Ash-Free Dry
Description: Applies to samples dried at a high temperature (e.g., in a furnace at 550 C) used in soil sediment and tissue weight determination

Name: Bulk Weight
Description: the (traditional) specific weight of a mixture including the empty spaces between the particulates.

Name: Dead
Description: Subject deceased, no blood sample; liver sample obtained

Name: Drained Weight
Description: The weight of the solid portion of the product with the liquid drained

Name: Dry
Description: The material dried in a dry oven

Name: Duplicate
Description: Second additional blood sample successfully obtained from subject

Name: Escaped
Description: Subject escaped trap or handlers prior to sampling attempt

Name: Freeze-Dried Wt
Description: The weight after freeze drying.

Name: Gravimetric Dry
Description: Gravimetric analysis describes a set of methods in analytical chemistry for the quantitative determination of an analyte based on the mass of a solid.

Name: Interstitial
Description: of, forming, or occupying interstices. an impurity found in the "pure" state. living in the spaces between individual sand grains in the soil or aquatic sediments

Name: Lipid
Description: The Lipid weight of a organism

Name: Not Sampled
Description: Blood sample not obtained from subject

Name: Recaptured
Description: Blood sample previously obtained from subject during monitoring activity, no further sampling

Name: Sampled
Description: Blood sample successfully obtained from subject

Name: Sieved Weight
Description: The weight after sieving.

Name: TSP
Description: Total suspended particles (TSP) is an archaic regulatory measure of the mass concentration of particulate matter (PM) in community air. It was defined by the (unintended) size-selectivity of the inlet

Name: Wet
Description: The wet weight of the material

Name: high wt
Description: high molecular weight; Soluble, Insoluble/non-water absorbing ("non-swellable"), Water absorbing ("swellable")

Name: low wt
Description: low molecular weight; a group of reactive chemoical, hypersensitivity, and direct toxicity
